Of these five places which Hierocles enumerates in succes· sion,lsinda and the people Perminodeis lie on the lstanoz Tchai, while the other three are in the valley of a tributary stream. While they form a group,and are therefore properly enumerated side by side, it is clear that the order in which Hierocles men· tions them is rather haphazard: but if we transpose his Σίνδοι and his Σινδαῦνδα, the order is true.
